<<<
For Christ also suffered once for sins, the juts for the unjust, that He might bring us to God, being put to death in the flesh but made alive by the Spirit
<<<
1 Peter 3:18 (NKJV)

Romans 3:21-22; 25-26

The righteousness of God has been made manifest. God is both the just and the justifier.

<<<
Therefore, since we have been justified by faith, we have peace with God through our Lord Jesus Christ.
<<<
Romans 5:1

Galatians 3:13-14

!! Salvation
God is telling Abraham how he will be a blessing. Genesis 15, God is the one who passes through the covenant. Isn't His word enough? But He does it regardless. Death is required for sin. He enforces His rules. The Angels gaze and gaze upon the Gospel.

Our supreme need is righteousness. We are born in sin.

Romans 3:21-22

!!! Substitution and Satisfaction
Jesus satisfied and demands of God's Holy Justice. As of substitute, He received God's wrath for us. That is why Jesus had to come to be born and be satisfied.

He received the wrath of God that we should have received.

<<<
Simul Justus Et Peccator
<<<
Martin Luther

Simultaneously Just and Sinner. This is a legal definition made by a just God.

!! Contrition
In order to appropriate the righteousness of Jesus, there must be contrition.

True and Godly Repentance. In order to appropriate, there is a turning from sin. I want to turn from a different life. Please save me and help me to live. Live a holy life from now on.

!! God is Just
Before God, there will be no unjust verdict. His justice will come about. But when He sees you and me, yes we will be guilty of Sin, we will hold the one who has paid the price of sin.

This is not just good news that we hold onto to ourselves, but the heart of our saviour is that He wishes us to believe. He has called us the ministry of reconciliation.